<p>Twice a year, the major fashion designers of the world meet in Milan to show their latest collections for the upcoming season. <strong>The International event Milano Moda Uomo</strong> presents the leading innovations of men’s prêt-à-porter explored by the most important maisons of Italian fashion, including Versace, Fendi, Missoni and Roberto Cavalli. From June 21st to 24th Corso Venezia, via Tortona, corso Monforte and via Senato were even more crowded with fashion than usual: fashion shows, events and appointments for the <strong>Milan Fashion Week</strong> - Milano Moda Uomo.</p>

<p>Classic denim looks for Miuccia Prada. Tropical adventures for Thomas Maier. Open shirts over softly tailored shorts for the bohemian travelers and surf culture of Angela Missoni. Suits with shorts in casual elegance for Giorgio Armani. Shoes without socks for the luxury brand of Diego Della Valle. <strong>Elegance and comfort, courage to wear colors, fashion against the crisis</strong>, that is the message of the Milan Fashion Week. </p>

